<subSubSection id="D87158AC2F1EFBF161B4CEE4FC9BACCD" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="notes">
<paragraph id="376C46B0012BF505BD4C8A7E8135F7C1" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D836662696F1C2F1831F07240F44720E" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
The two Chilean species differ macroscopically, 
<taxonomicName id="189B18BA34724A5372A5BCB1B81D53B1" genus="B." lsidName="B. magellanicus" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" rank="species" species="magellanicus">
<emphasis id="E634AAC18A77D4354290AA834177AE05" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">B. magellanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
having noticeably thinner stipes than 
<taxonomicName id="96788254B9CC360DF6BE2DD8BC6392F8" genus="B." lsidName="B. osornoensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" rank="species" species="osornoensis">
<emphasis id="767A79E6D03EE3F7838045046B209510" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">B. osornoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The only known collection of 
<taxonomicName id="7D52E10B1DA5CCC7474F9349A9A60513" genus="B." lsidName="B. magellanicus" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" rank="species" species="magellanicus">
<emphasis id="C8C275E1762C29E475B9ECFE467C2AF7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">B. magellanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is from Magellanic subpolar forest in Patagonia that is dominated by 
<taxonomicName id="887060A601D9AC87C208AB351FF0EA17" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Clavicipitaceae" genus="Nothofagus" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Nothofagus betuloides" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="betuloides">
<emphasis id="DC0246BB6818E5C2379F6DFA265BB6C2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Nothofagus betuloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is possible that this 
<taxonomicName id="4030A09CB29B44B5763B922863342F6B" authority="P.R.Johnst., 2021" authorityName="P.R.Johnst." authorityYear="2021" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Nothofagaceae" genus="Brahmaculus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Brahmaculus" order="Helotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BCA93DD45E5BCA44500E689C6AD57125" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Brahmaculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species is restricted to these sub Antarctic cold southern forests but more specimens are needed to determine the range of the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
